The user identified it — it's the `.skip-link` element. Let me check its styling.

The skip-link is styled in `site-shared.css` lines 36-51:

```css
.skip-link {
  position: absolute;
  top: -40px;
  ...
  background: var(--accent);  /* #CCC3F8 — light purple! */
}
```

It's supposed to be hidden off-screen (`top: -40px`) and only appear on `:focus`. But something is causing it to be partially visible. Let me check the exact rendering.

